,Recommended,233150,31909225,Posted: 22 May,all,Gungrounds Games,"An excellent feel of flight, maneuvering, and destruction - I felt as though I was a top pilot fighting through dozens of enemy airplanes. The visual style is perfect for this type of game.Each rauser consists of three main parts - weapon, body, and engine. There are five versions of each part which the player chooses freely in order to assemble their rauser. This translates to 125 combinations of planes.Each mission requires the player to use a particular loadout, which makes it fun to try out different combinations. Plane components are visually distinct and also affect the music which makes using each rauser unique.Some problems I encountered:-certain weapons require the player to take some time to understand the mechanics-steep learning curve (depending on user preference)-apart form mission completion and unlocking of components there is not a lot of unlockable content, but given that different components allow different missions, there should always be enough room to play a different mission if stuckEven though the game is short, I believe that the sheer quality justifies the high price tag. It is crucial to invest enough time to fully understand the game, and get a feel for it. If you manage that, it won’t be long before you love it forever.Vlambeer has been our major source of inspiration, and one of the reasons why we started making shooter games. I hope they will not mind, but because it is so hard to reach players these days I want to mention our newest game Rocking Pilot which is in some ways similar to Luftrausers. We would be humbled if you would check it out and share us your impressions. Thanks!http://store.steampowered.com/app/593680/Rocking_Pilot/"
