,Recommended,233150,32233774,Posted: 6 June,all,Spookicidal Tendencies,"This is one of the few bullet hell games I really enjoy. All of the different weapons, bodies, and engines really make it so you can have a different experience each time you play. There are enough unlocks to hold your interest for quite a while and the difficulty level is low enough at the start for inexperienced players (like myself) to enjoy short fast paced games, but ramps up high enough that you can put as many hours as you want into the game perfecting it. There's even a more hardcore mode that just amps the difficulty up to 11 from the start. Good for players that want to skip the easy starting bit. The soundtrack is also awesome and totally gets you in the mood."
