,Recommended,233150,22823963,"Posted: 6 May, 2016",all,fri_freeman,"If you're like me, you might be always wondering if there's something hidden within this game. I always thought this game looks really simple, too simple, from the previews. But it got such good reviews. Is there something else hidden within?Answer: There is not. It's exactly how it is in the previews. It's a gravity-based shmup, with multiplier-based scoring, stylistic and simplistic artstyle with one sephia shade within one stage without any story at all.But goddamn it is fun. The shooting is really satisfying, unlocking new parts feels really make a difference, and the contextual bgm really kick♥♥♥♥♥This game is really the crowning achievement of ""Let's play this for five minutes... whelp it's 1 hour already.""But there really isn't many content in this game, so that's that. After you unlock all parts and do all missions (challenges), you only try to beat high score. Strangely, I think this game would be more fulfilling to those who are not that good in this kind of shmup game, because they'll have longer time unlocking everything. But of course shmup veteran would get a kick from trying to beat high scores.Basically, recommended, but buy this discounted if you're concerned with the small amount of content."
