,Recommended,233150,9543683,"Posted: 18 March, 2014",all,Gabaz,"Its really REALLY good.You play as a completly insane German (maybe Austrian?) fighter pilot, who has the job of burining the skies in his ""Luft Rauser"", when you die you respawn at your battleship, where humourously characatured German generals, nurses and mad scientists brief you on your stats, missions and new abilities, something about it makes you feel that kind of ""Being bad is good"" feeling that you may have got from other games.The graphics and setting are steller, and really add to the insane atmosphere. The Music is superb and exhilarating, constantly pushing you forward. Think Hotline Miami music, but in the skies.The gameplay is where the game outshines every other aspect. There is no use of mouse here, just the keyboard for those of you who want to play this in you bed or on the train/bus or something.The movement and momentum that you get from flying is something which reminds me of the responsiveness of Super Meat Boy, it just ""feels"" right. It feels like you are moving an actual (very flexible) plane, where you are flinging it about using the momentum, only sometimes turining the engine on to move from place to place.There is use of a mission system which gives a little but more meaning behind the carnage, and completing these allows you to unlock new features for your plane, and each of these features does a good job of changing the feel, without causing you to relearn the game.Finally, do not worry about repitition, as it that there is quite alot of random generation, so it is always impossible to get used to where the enemy is coming from.I absolutly recommend this game, and at the current price point, i'd say go ahead and buy it at full price."
