76561198010932791,Recommended,233150,16487497,"Posted: 17 June, 2015",all,TheDanman,"I'm recommending LUFTRAUSERS because there is no button in between ""Yes"" and ""No"".The Good:The core mechanics of this game are very well implemented which results in game-feel that you just keep wanting more of. The combination of the excellent camera, sound, and gratifying pixel explosions make shooting and movement a blast. The different ship parts that you can unlock are also well designed: each one is unique and, more importantly, they can synergize in interesting ways. The music track that changes according to your combination of ship parts is a delightful touch.The Bad:Progression in LUFTRAUSERS is awkward. In one of my early playthroughs I spotted a Blimp and I believed it was the first of many ""boss"" type enemies that I would encounter. After it promptly destroyed me, and after several more unsuccessful attempts to encounter it again, I began to wonder how many of these bosses there were; how much harder could this game possibly get? It turns out Blimps are the first and final boss and they are unbelievably hard to take down. So I turned my gaze to the ""missions"" that each ship part presents (""Kill 3 Submarines"", ""Score 10000 points"" etc). After about an hour and a half I had unlocked every ship part and now my only real remaining goal was to take down a damn blimp. My remaining 2 hours in the game have been enjoyable due to the game's great core mechanics, but I have made no progress after unlocking the last ship part.The Ugly:The menu is pretty bad.  It does not adjust input text for a gamepad and it obfuscates information. I was told many times that I had unlocked something but it was not clear what I had unlocked. I was told to enable this mystery unlock in the ""options"" menu but this options menu was nowhere to be found. It turns out the things I had been unlocking were different color palettes for the game, a few of which were so hideous I am surprised they are even included as an option.tl;dr+ Top notch game-feel+ Great audio- Lack of content / game progression- Poorly designed menus"
,Recommended,233150,10941093,"Posted: 29 June, 2014",all,Tametman,"Nice mechanics, nice retro atmosphere but not good enough.. (but it is still a good game)7 out of 10"
