76561198025245158,Recommended,233150,12257348,"Posted: 27 September, 2014",all,Killer Whales,"Very simple and yet so much fun. In it's madness, there's no doubt that it is easy to get frustrated, but it's surprising how good you can get. I'd still call myself mediocre at best, but it was great."
,Recommended,233150,9604120,"Posted: 23 March, 2014",all,Nymlus,"Luftrausers is surprisingly good. Incredibly good, even. You start it up for the first time and within a minute of playing it you'll be smiling broadly and wishing that every game could be as viscerally enjoyable as this one.The controls have been honed to perfection. Simply flying around with the aircraft (is it called a Luftrauser?) is pleasing to the senses. Throughout the game, you'll unlock new parts that you can use to customize your plane, which come with both benefits and drawbacks. Here's where the true brilliance of the design comes in. Each part of the ship has its own instruments to add to the song that plays during the game, and each part has multiple missions that you can only complete with that part. So each combination of parts - and there's at least a hundred - offers a unique experience. To top it all off, every aircraft you can possibly assemble with these components has its own nickname, such as the Nightmare, the Tuberauser, or my current favorite, the Warturtle.It's cheap, it's intense, and it's extremely challenging. If you like shooters of any kind, consider Luftrausers a solid purchase."
