,Recommended,233150,11182756,"Posted: 11 July, 2014",all,+Sputnik+,"Relive the harrowing experience of flying in the Pacific during World War 2 in this incredibly realistic military flight simulator that rival's the genre's best (Microsoft Combat Simulator, X-Wing vs Tie Fighter). Fly in dozens of different real life planes, painstakingly rendered in lush 3D using hundreds of references taken from the Smithsonian's air museum.For added realism, use a wireless keyboard with low batteries. You'll never know when the keyboard stops responding, representing an engine stall that American pilots often faced in the heat of battle due to the low quality of their engine parts."
