,Recommended,233150,9632430,"Posted: 26 March, 2014",all,reckhou,"LUFTRAUSERS is not like any other flying shooting game - it has a ""Roguelike"" genre, but it's fun, way more fun than other Roguelike games. The biggest issue of Roguelike game is player often dies randomly with little or none character progression. You keep dying in this game too, but this game is not much repeative than other games. Players can try different kinds of plane builds, every build is combined with 3 parts: Weapon, Body & Engine. Each of them got unique attributes, so try to build your own plane & find set up suits you best can cost you hours.Also, this game has a progress system that you can unlock different kinds of parts each time you raised to a new level. So it's not boring after died many times, at least an aim is set. The game progress is well balanced so you can get your new gear just before you are a little bit of tired, that makes you spend another 15 minutes to try your shiny new gear.The last and the most important is LUFTRAUSERS also has awesome gameplay with simulated 2D physics. Each kind of plane has its own physical parameter. You can get these in *.json files under game folder, adjust them as well. Game control only need 5 keys(4 directions + fire) and it works just fine. The core mechanism is simple, but being well made and adjusted. It must took producers lots of time. I have to say this game worth its price and it won't let you down."
