,Recommended,233150,10734050,"Posted: 23 June, 2014",all,Pomme ⒼⓔⓝⓞⓩⓘⓓⒺ,"Although LUFTRAUSERS is not a SHMUPin the traditional sense, I'm still gonna call it'SHMUP ON DRUG'due to it's bullet hell and thre adrenaline rush.The gameplay is simple yet clever and addictive. You try to stay alive using customizable parts to suit your own play style. The 'stop-shooting-to-regenerate-health' mechanic keeps you focus on the most important part, KILL and STAY ALIVE, rather than putting you in difficult situations where you died just because you need to grab 'that healing item'The control is very responsive, although a bit confusing at first (if you're used to the six/eight axis free movement implemented in modern games), in LUFTRUASERS, you use LEFT/RIGHT to pivot/rotate your plane and UP to use the throttle/forward, but once you get used to it (and learned to master the control for the part combination you of your choice), you'll be going for the kill!AWESOME MUSICS"
