76561197975142481,Not Recommended,233150,19441252,"Posted: 2 December, 2015",all,Shivershorts,"This will mostly echo other negative reviews but here goes.Luftrausers in itself is a great game. The controls are tight, the action is fun, and the customization is interesting. However, it's insane that what amounts to a flash game that you would find for free on the internet is sold for $10 on Steam. After a couple of hours, this game completely lost its momentum. It started out great, but it's so shallow that it made me angry that I paid $2 for it on sale.The challenges get to the point that they are too hard to have fun. I don't know how to trigger blimp appearances or make submarines show up, but when the challenge involves destroying one of those specific enemies, the frustration becomes unbearable. It ultimately just becomes a repetitious chore, and the fact that there is only one song during gameplay (which starts over every time you start a new game) doesn't help.Luftrausers is the second game I've ever bought that wound up on my ""hidden"" list in my games library."
