76561198025902156,Not Recommended,233150,21100028,"Posted: 10 February, 2016",all,(AB) Slow Moth,"Luftrausers is a fun little game. The game feel is excellent, the aesthetic and general presentation is well put together, and the game mechanics are clever, simple, and engaging (see the Steam video to understand all you need to know). Unfortunately, the game's progression, while paced well, is quickly plateaued. Within an hour or so, you should unlock most of the unlockable parts. This isn't bad in and of itself, but after this, there isn't much incentive to continue except the high score. The UI is also pretty awkward and clunky, with virtually no options, and poor gamepad support.If you like like shooting for high scores, by all means, you may very well spend hours in this game. But for people who don't, this may feel a little too empty to warrant a full price purchase."
