,Recommended,233150,9555773,"Posted: 18 March, 2014",all,anthropic,"Last March I discovered Vlambeer's Ridiculous Fishing and it became my first essential smartphone game.  What makes it so compelling is that the game starts simple, yet tough and the proceeds to reward you with dozens of neat perks to slightly break the game urging you to greater depths and new areas.Luftrausers has the same formula and it's freaking brilliant.  It controls not unlike an old Lunar Lander game.  It's tough to fly and in addition your being shot at from every direction.  But it suddenly rewards you with great plane customizations (""parts"") that break the game is slight, yet brilliant ways.  An engine that shoots bullets behind you, where you're not aiming.  Armor that lets you not take melee damage, at the expense of health.  An armor that explodes when you die, killing everything on screen.  The combination of the ""parts"" is up to you.In order to nudge you into trying new parts combinations there are a progression of missions for each part, and that's why you'll keep coming back for more.Vlambeer has once again shown that they are masters."
