,Recommended,233150,17105532,"Posted: 18 July, 2015",all,VintageTsundere,"Disclosure: I haven't ""Completed"" the game per se but have played enough to understand it.Luftrausers is a game where you play as a single plane taking on a near impossible task. It's you vs everything. The entire game is essentially a massive ""Objective: Survive"".There are roughly 9 different enemies in the game. The consist of different things like planes, ""Aces"" which are super-powered planes, and (Blank, not putting the full name, since it makes it a tad obvious what they do.) aces which are super powered aces. (Scary♥♥♥♥♥♥. There is also boats, battleships, submarines and the acemarine. (Real scary♥♥♥♥♥♥. Then you have the blimp. You're on your own to find out what each of these things do how ever.The game has a form of loadout system, using 3 parts. The gun, the body and the propulsion. Part of the fun in this game is finding different insane combinations and seeing how long you'll last. The body will for instance make you slower, but with more health, or faster with little health. I personally like to play as a glass cannon, going at mach speeds, but get scratched and I die. Can lead to some fun or frustrating playthroughs.There's enough variation to keep the game fresh how ever I can say from personal experience that I feel that it's a ""Go To"" game. When you have moments where you just want to hop on and play a game. No story or anything like that, just pure gameplay. Each playthrough is relatively short and depends on your skill. Sometimes a minute, sometimes 10. All depends on you.The standard music is pretty great. You'll be flying down from the sky, about to take out a battle ship and the music peaks up. It really feels great, when moments like that happens.There's 2 difficulty modes from what I can see. SFMT and Normal. Essentially, hear sirens and cry. You can periodically unlock new colour schemes for the game but I didn't think any of them match up with the original, how ever if you're looking for a new experience after playing for a while. Maybe just changing the colours is all you need.Conclusion, if you're looking for a game which you can keep coming back to, that doesn't take a lot of your time, yet has enough replay value for multiple playthroughs then this is a pretty decent game. I reccomend trying it out, and if you're still skeptical then wait for a sale. It was roughly 2-3 pounds when I bought it, which is a pretty nice price."
