76561198073492048,Recommended,233150,17538609,"Posted: 14 August, 2015",all,TANKMAN606,"This game is a love/hate relationship, it hates you bu sending hoardes of various difficult to kill enemies to attack you and you hate it when you lose to them meanwhile it loves you when you succeed in doing a challenge and gives you something in return and you love it because you are happy that you won and you feel badass..............then you hate each other to death again."
,Recommended,233150,17539260,"Posted: 14 August, 2015",all,uGryzzli,The most fun you can have with your pants on!
,Recommended,233150,17540615,"Posted: 14 August, 2015",all,Bond of Travolta,"Surprisingly very fun arcade-y game.I'm always skeptical when in comes to pseudo-retro games, especially ones with lo-fi graphics, but obviously this is among the good ones. Basically, you pilot a plane, avoiding bullets & missiles while shooting down your many adversaries. As you play & achieve things, you are rewarded with new plane parts interchangeable in-between runs (runs are basically infinite and can only be renewed when you die). These parts are divided into weaponry, body & thruster.However, newer parts are not necessarily superior. All parts comes with their own pluses & minuses, based on the special property it carries (like a body made of a nuclear warhead, yeah, go figure). So it depends on your combination & how you play them.Equipping certain parts also means you are only allowed to unlock certain achievements. However, this can also be used to your advantage. For example, one of the achievement missions  for the basic machine gun would be to take down a battleship. This is to say, a rather impossible task. However, if you equip your plane with the nuclear warhead body while also equpping the machine gun, you can simply run into the ship to kill it, you, and everything else on the screen and there you have it. One battleship down while 'using' the machine gun.The game doesn't have any story, but it doesn't need one anyways. The setting is enough to give you the idea that it's a war, and you are just one among the many disposable soldiers.That said, due to the nature of the game it probably has low lasting appeal. However, due to its simplicity (doesn't necessarily mean it's easy though, far from it) it's also an easy pick up and play for when you just want to play a game but isn't in the mood to think much, but still wants more or less a challenge. If you don't have a game like that in your library yet, you might want to get this."
