76561198030549296,Recommended,233150,14311160,"Posted: 3 February, 2015",all,iloshwdgac,"Graphics: 2/3Story: 1/3Game Play: 3/3Re-playable: 1/1Sale Rate: 20%Total: 7/10Graphics: 2/3The game has a clean Indy style focusing on brown scale tones with large bullets so you can easily see and sometimes dodge them. Your own plane looks different enough that it doesn’t get lost in the fighting without it looking foolish and too cartoony. Everything sticks nicely to the games aesthetic and it looks like an old arcade machine.The music has a marching drive to it, spurring you on. There is a weird choice to make the music track restart on launch so if you die in the first few seconds you hear a sharp stop and start of the soundtrack.Story: 1/3As far as I can tell, you are a German flying the most advance plane in the war. The evil Churchill has declared total war against the Glorious Third Reich and only you can stop his relentless assault over the British Channel. You fight not for glory or for riches, you fight for the survival of your glorious empire.I don’t know if this was made by Germans or someone simply said, “you know what we have too much of? The Allies' side of the war. Let’s change that”. It wasn’t until I killed Churchill in his war zeppelin that I realized I was playing as a German.Since this is a score attack rogue-like game, it doesn’t need a story or dialog to keep you playing. It does create a uniform world with some discovery, but no great mystery. Doesn’t add or subtract anything.Game Play: 3/3This game gives some great visuals to assist your gameplay. There is no health bar or ammo, thereis only the dog fight. There is no power ups or health drops, there is only the dog fight. There are no allies, there is only the dog fight.When you take damage, the screen starts to get narrower. To regen health, you just stop shooting. Enemies play by the same rules as you, when you crash you lose health, but you might kill the enemy. To accomplish this your plane can maintain speed after you stop thrusting. So you can fly across the screen while shooting backwards.The controls are tight and the feedback is instant. There is a large number of supported play styles with different planes geared directly for. At a certain point you get a randomizer to add a new element to the game.Re-Playability: 1/1You unlock new parts after you die, and there is one plane body that turns you into a nuke on death.Should you buy it?I had more fun playing this with friends than alone. Has some good value, but nothing world changing, buy on a lite sale.Note: single player only, you need friends in room."
