,Recommended,233150,32717951,Posted: 24 June,all,theredpwny,"This is a great game with interesting mechanics and a nice progression system.You're a single plane blowing up other planes, boats, submarines, blimps, etc. You use one key to shoot, one to boost/thrust, and two keys to rotate left and right.The controls can take some getting used to as they're basically ""tank""/Asteroids controls. At first they don't feel very tight because you can only move by rotating the plane and pressing up to thrust. Once you get used to them though, the controls are alright.You can customize your plane's gun, body, and engine. You'll soon find favorite combinations, but the challenges to unlock more parts encourages experimenting with other loadouts.The game also has palette swaps and great music.Overall it's a great game, albeit with a bit of a learning curve for the controls."
