,Recommended,233150,14928626,"Posted: 16 March, 2015",all,SnacksCCM,"1.) Get a box.2.) Add one copy of Metal Slug (Neo Geo).3.) Add a copy of 1943 from your local arcade (Raiden Trad is probably too flashy).4.) Add some great electronica music (with a taste of the soundtrack from ""Command & Conquer: Red Alert"" for PC).5.) Throw in an Atari 2600 ""Asteroids"" cartridge.6.) Ask Marceline (of ""Adventure Time"" fame) to devour any particularly rich/vibrant colors from the box.7.) Shake vigorously for 10 minutes.Enjoy the result: Luftrausers.I'd score it: 8/10. Sound is fantastic. Graphics are simple, but effective (and it's obviously on purpose). It's challenging, but rewarding - each plane combination has its own music track to fly by and there are a bunch of interesting combinations. Gameplay is fluid and fun, but the replay value is only so-so. There are also some mildly frustrating parts to the game (like trying to maintain combos or figuring out the conditions in which certain enemies will appear, seemingly underpowered weapons, etc.), however those (at least in part) are also what makes it challenging.Worth the scratch to buy it? Yes."
