,Recommended,233150,28705149,"Posted: 27 December, 2016",all,2bfx,"Bought the product after I watched a talk by one of the founders of Vlambeer, the publishing company, at GDC.He sounded like someone who knows how to release great games and mentioned Luftrausers and lots of other Vlambeer games, but not in a cheesy way. Product placement done right, really.So I gave it a try. It *might* have appealed to me as a German, the title gave me a good chuckle.Not disappointed, this game is fun for 5 minutes or fun for 5 hours (can't tell for days and weeks yet) and made me watch out for other Vlambeer releases.I have fun playing it. My girlfriend will love it. My 6-year old niece will love it. My dog will not notice the reduced color palette. It's a family game at its best, really.Most impressive about Luftrausers: it feels and looks hilarious when you play it, but the objects for themselves actually are as pixel-minimal as it gets. They get their characteristics from a combination of sound, minute details in animations, and physics that hit the sweet spot of goofiness right between the eyes. Masterpiece!"
