76561198076399560,Recommended,233150,33812211,Posted: 26 July,all,Skelzie,"While everything about this game - the graphics, the music, the core gameplay - is great, it truly shines in customization.You have complete control over how your plane works, but no combination is unbalanced. Want to make a ship that takes lots of damage and dishes out death? Go for it, but be aware that your ship might move slower and offer you less time to dodge. Want a plane that specializes in ramming through boats? I guess you can do that! A plane that hovers in the sky and spins around firing lasers and dropping bombs? Sure!The myriad customization options keep me coming back to this game, whether it's to shoot up some baddies in my favorite armored death machine or if it's to try something new, like a ship that shoots ~10 bullets per second. Every run is as different as you want it to be.As far as the core mechanics, everything about this game justfeelsright. Things explode in satisfying ways, the controls are responsive if a bit (purposefully) unwieldy, and none of the options you can use for your plane will make you frustrated at how bad their disadvantages are. It is clear that the developers spent a lot of time fine-tuning things to make every run satisfying and fun."
